          "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"><head>
<title>Incoming Orders_Invoice</title>
<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css"/>
</head>
<body>
<p></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:13pt"><b>Incoming Orders - Invoice</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></p>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Use the Invoice screen to create invoices for the Customer Orders.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">In order to create a Invoice, assign invoice number, choose the items in the invoice (with its 
quantity, discount etc), key in the total discount, applicable tax,surcharge, Adjustments etc. Once 
all the details are provided, either Save as Draft (Temporary save) or proceed to Save it and print 
it or send to the Customer.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Invoice Number </b>: The Invoice number is an auto-generated value which increments by 1 for each 
new invoice.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Due Date:</b> Choose the Due Date by when the payment should be received from Customer.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Customer</b> : This field is automatically populated from the Customer information mentioned in the 
current Order. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Order Number</b> : This field is automatically populated from the Order information mentioned in the 
current Order. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Handler</b> :&#160; Select the User name who is raising this invoice. It can be same as the current logged 
in user or it can be another user on whose behalf this invoice is being raised.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Items Section - </b>The Products and Services that are being invoiced are chosen from this section. 
Each item has fields like Category, Item ID, Item Description, Unit Price, Quantity, Base 
Price,Discount, Total etc. By default, the products and services mentioned in the Current Order 
are displayed. You can either add to the same, remove any product or service or modify the 
details of displayed items like Quantity, Unit Price etc. However please note that if you modify the 
Unit Price, it does not change the <b>Unit Price</b> of the Customer(Incoming) Order.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">If you wish to remove any items (i.e Product or service or subscription), you can do so by moving 
the mouse pointer near to the required item and then clicking on the <b>Delete </b>button that appears 
below the same. This action will remove that item from the Invoice - Item section.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Click the <b>+Add button</b> to start adding new items to the Invoice. You can only add the products or 
services available in the current Customer(Incoming) Order. The only additional category that can 
be added are new subscriptions. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Select Category</b> : As you can only add Subscriptions (in addition) to those items already available 
in the screen, choose the <b>Subscription</b> in Select Category. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Item code</b> : The Item code relevant for the chosen Category can be chosen from the Drop down 
list.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Unit Price : </b>Enter the Unit Price of the Subscription(Ex : Monthly subscription fees if the invoice is 
generated monthly or the subscription fees applicable for the entire subscription period, if the 
invoice is being generated for the whole period).</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Quantity: </b>Enter the Quantity (Note : In case of monthly invoice, the Quantity can be 1 or if the 
subscription period is 4 months and the total period is invoiced, then the Quantity will be 4 in that 
case. Alternatively if the subscription fee is 1 full amount then the Quantity will be 1 and the Unit 
Price will be the full subscription fees. Example : If a Course is 6 months and the full fees is INR. 
50000,if the invoice is generated for the whole amount,&#160; then in this case, Quantity will be 1 and 
the Unit Price can be INR 50,000).</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Base Price</b> : The Base Price gets automatically calculated by the System for the chosen Item. 
This is calculated by multiplying the Quantity sold with the Unit Price.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Discount</b> : Not applicable for the subscription category.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Tax</b> : Not applicable for the subscription category. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Total : </b>The Total Value for the current item is displayed here (Total = Base Price - Discount + 
Tax)</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">In the similar manner, you can add more items in the invoice. Click on the <b>+Add </b>button at the right 
hand corner across the <b>Items </b>Section to add additional items to the invoice.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">In case you do not need any item that you have created in the Invoice, you can use the <b>Delete</b> 
button below the current item details in the invoice. The <b>Delete </b>button automatically appears when 
you move your mouse pointer on the required item detail. <b>Delete</b> action removes the entire line 
item from the invoice.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To proceed with entry of other items, use the <b>+Add</b> button.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Once you have entered all the items in the invoice, you can start adding the levies and charges 
applicable for the entire invoice.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Surcharge</b>: You can include applicable surcharges for the invoice. Click <b>+Add</b> Button to add 
surcharges. Clicking on the <b>+Add </b>button will create a new empty row to add the surcharges. 
Provide the details for <b>Surcharge Name, Surcharge Type(Percentage or Amount). </b>Depending 
on your selection the application allows you to either enter the<b> Surcharge Percentage or 
Amount</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To add more Surcharges, click the <b>+Add </b>Button.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To fully remove any surcharge item, click on the <b>Delete</b> Button that appears below the surcharge 
item when you move your mouse pointer near the surcharge item. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Invoice level discounts</b>: Use this section to define discounts that are applicable for the whole 
invoice. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Click <b>+Add</b> Button to add the Invoice level discounts. Clicking on the <b>+Add </b>button will create a 
new empty row to add the the discounts. Provide the details for <b>Discount, Discount 
Type(Percentage or Amount). </b>Depending on your selection the application allows you to either 
enter the<b> Discount Percentage or Amount</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To add more <b>Discounts</b>, click the <b>+Add </b>Button.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To fully remove any Discount item, click on the <b>Delete</b> Button that appears below the Discount 
item when you move your mouse pointer near Discount item. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Adjustments:</b>If there are any adjustments to be made(Ex : Miscellaneous charges or any other 
kinds of deductions based on past transactions) to this invoice, you can use this field to record the 
same. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Click <b>+Add</b> Button to add the Adjustments. Clicking on the <b>+Add </b>button will create a new empty 
row to add the the Adjustments. Provide the details for<b> Add or Subtract </b>(choose Add for 
recording Increase Adjustment, choose Subtract for recording a Decrease Adjustment)<b>, Amount 
</b>(Adjustment Amount)<b>, Description</b>(Details about the reason for Adjustment)<b>. </b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To add more <b>Adjustments</b>, click the <b>+Add </b>Button.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">To fully remove any <b>Adjustments</b> item, click on the <b>Delete</b> Button that appears below the 
<b>Adjustments</b> item when you move your mouse pointer near the same. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Below fields are automatically calculated by the Application and display only fields.</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Sub Total : </b>The sum of <b>Total </b>field in the <b>Items </b>Section.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Total Base Price: </b>The sum of <b>Base Price </b>field in the <b>Items </b>Section</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Total Discount:</b> The sum of <b>Invoice level Discounts</b> Section</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Total Tax :</b> The sum of <b>Tax </b>field in the <b>Items </b>Section.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Total Surcharge:</b> The sum of the <b>Amount </b>field in the <b>Surcharges </b>Section</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Adjustment : </b>The sum of net(Increase-Decrease) <b>Adjustments</b> Section</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Grand Total : </b>The <b>Grand</b> <b>total</b> is a calculated by using the above mentioned calculated fields 
based on the below formula :</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Sub Total </b>+ <b>Total Tax </b>+<b>Total</b> <b>Surcharge</b> + <b>Adjustments</b>- <b>Total Discount</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Documents : </b>Use this section to attach any relevant document to the Invoice. Click on <b>+Upload</b> 
to start uploading documents from your system. The application opens the standard Windows File 
Open dialog box. Choose the folder and then the file that needs to be uploaded. Click on Open 
button. Now you can see the chosen file being attached with this invoice. In this way you can 
attach more than 1 file to the current invoice. Once you have attached the relevant files,&#160; You can 
remove any of this attachment by clicking on the <b>Delete B</b>utton below the attached file.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Payment Received : </b>If the full Payment is being collected at the time of invoice creation or has 
already been collected, you can check the &quot;Payment Received&quot; Checkbox. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">The application asks for the below 2 information namely :</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Select Payment Mode: </b>Choose the Payment mode (Ex: Cash, Cheque, Debit Card, Credit Card 
etc) from the drop down list.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Enter the following information for Payment mode other than <b>Cash.</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Bank Account :</b> Bank Account number </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Reference Number: </b>Enter the Transaction Reference number</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Payment Date: </b>Choose the Date of receipt of the payment. If the payment was received in 
advance, choose an earlier date or if it is just being received at the time of invoice generation, 
choose the invoice date as the Payment Date. Use the <b>Calendar </b>dialog box to select the date.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Clicking on the <b>Payment Received</b> field will internally create a receipt for the invoice. This facility 
can be used only when the customer pays or has paid the full amount of the invoice.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">On completion of entry of the above fields , you can press any one of the below mentioned 
buttons : </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Send :</b> Press this button when you have finalized the invoice and wish to send it to the Customer. 
Once this button is pressed, the Invoice details are saved in the application and it is marked to be 
shown in the &quot;Dashboard Section (Status-&gt;Unpaid Invoice subsection)&quot; when the Customer logs 
in. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Save and Print</b>: Press this button when you have completed the invoice and wish to save the 
details in the application and also print the invoice.&#160; In this case, the Invoice will not be marked to 
be displayed in the &quot;Dashboard Section&quot; when the customer logs in.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Print:</b> Press this button when you wish to take a printout of the invoice. The details will not get 
stored in the application. You can continue adding/modifying details in the invoice.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Close:</b> Press this button when you wish to close the Invoice screen. If you have not pressed the 
&quot;Save as Draft&quot; or &quot;Send&quot; or &quot;Save and Print&quot;, the details in the screen are ignored(i.e not saved) 
and the Invoice screen gets closed and you will be taken back to the Customer Order Listing 
Section.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"><br />
</font></div>
